{"id":521768552,"lang":"python3","time":"1Â year","timestamp":1626162501,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"3732 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/521768552/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"3Sum","memory":"17.5 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def threeSum(self, nums: List[int]) -> List[List[int]]:\n        \n        #didn't use dict because of sorted output\n        nums.sort()\n        res=set()\n        for i in range(len(nums)):\n            target=0-nums[i]\n            d={}\n            for j in range(i+1,len(nums)):\n                x=target-nums[j]\n                if x in d:\n                    res.add((nums[i],nums[j],nums[d[x]]))\n                else:\n                    d[nums[j]]=j\n                    \n        return res\n        \n","compare_result":"","title_slug":"3sum"}
